# Goal

Replace the per-(token, head) softmax-over-keys attention kernel with
a FlashAttention-style block-tiled streaming softmax + accumulation.

# Background

For each token, head, ROCm computes
  - load Q
  - for each key k: dot(Q, K[k]), apply mask
  - softmax over n_keys
  - weighted sum of V[k] by softmax probabilities

Metal uses block-tiled FA: stream K/V in tiles, maintain online softmax
(running max + running denom), no materialized n_keys-wide attention
matrix. This:
  - reads K and V once per Q tile (vs once per token)
  - keeps the softmax state in registers/LDS, no n_keys spill
  - allows multiple heads/tokens to share K/V tile loads

