# Approach

1. Start with raw-KV prefill path. Block tile: BR Q rows x BC K cols
   per threadblock. Each block streams K and V columns, maintains
   running (m_i, l_i, acc_i) per Q row, writes final O = acc / l.
   Reference ggml/llama.cpp HIP FA implementations.

2. Validate against existing kernel via tests/ds4_rocm_kernel_test.c.
   The existing harness is the canonical correctness oracle.

3. Extend to compressed-KV and decode paths.

